comments:
Build ID: M20060921-0945

Steps To Reproduce:
1.This error is only on Java 1.6.0.  It will function correctly in Java 1.5.x.

2. Set up a new Dynamic Web Project with Tomcat 5.5.20 or 5.5.4 as the Server and Java 1.6.0 as the JRE.  No need to create a html or jsp page.  If you have an existing web project it should display the problem too.  But my point is it errors straight out of the box on a new install of Eclipse and a new Dynamic web project. 

3. Right click on the new project and press run as ->run on Server.  (any run command on server command will do.)

4. The console displays a stack trace(displayed below). The server proceeds to the started state but does not serve any pages.  

Other notes:  Window Vista RC1 , build 5600.

I hope this helps.  Thank you for your time and dedication to Eclipse.  I don't want anyone else to have this nightmare.

Fishjd.
